<subSubSection id="D680E2A7F43B12DA43797F8329B8D7CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DF09B59D4C47968E2160A950BBB7F34D" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35A99FD371CB4F9E977B7A04E9AADE5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
Female (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="13527897C1D2217FAA7F7FCA29BE5399" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">20</figureCitation>
) body length 5.5-7.0 mm, forewing length 5.5-6.5 mm; male (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AEA159765F18940B541C58357E3EB213" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">21</figureCitation>
) body length 5.5-5.7 mm, forewing length 4.7-5.5 mm; black, with the following parts orange or yellow: most of mandible, two small lateral spots at the base of clypeus, male clypeus yellow except outer margin, longitudinal interantennal spot, scape ventrally and flagella ventrally (or not), a small spot of ocular sinus, a line behind eyes at gena, an anterior band of pronotum, tegula (except brownish red middle), parategula, metanotum, apices of fore and mid femora dorsally, irregular spots of fore and mid tibiae, apical bands of T1-T2 and S2 (sometimes break); head and mesosoma with very coarse punctures, interspaces strongly reticulate; clypeus flat in the middle part, with lateral longitudinal raised carina at apex, and with fine sparse punctures, and punctures at apex larger and deeper, or even longitudinally striate, apical margin somewhat emarginated and almost truncated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="71DB3C95E5195A129FD8095530173633" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">22</figureCitation>
); male clypeus with fine sparse punctures, apical margin moderately emarginated, transparent, laterally forming a short tooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="212834BA260161784207360A9227C77A" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">23</figureCitation>
); male A13 about 2.7 times as long as basal width, flat, curved, and widen at the apex, backward reaching base of A11 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="13071EFF53CEB4F9B81DC44BAFA9CAF8" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">25</figureCitation>
); occipital carina distinctly sinuate and almost incised in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="291AE581FB0CA0E81181F746F265E761" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">24</figureCitation>
); anterior face of pronotum concave weakly, with two almost coalesced weak foveae (Fig. 
